{"questionId":"29568780","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Malvern Aquatic Center hosted a 3 metre spring board diving event. The judges, Stan and&nbsp;Minsun awarded 8 competitors a score out of 10. The raw data is collated in the following table.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/41660f346839c99278354bd970ea1e2685082f38.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Write down the equation of the regression line <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span> on <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = 1.14x + 0.578\\,\\,\\left( {y = 1.14033 \\ldots x + 0.578183 \\ldots } \\right)\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1.14</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>0.578</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mo>=</mo>\n      <mn>1.14033</mn>\n      <mo>…</mo>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mn>0.578183</mn>\n      <mo>…</mo>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><strong>Note</strong>: Award <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"1.14x\">\n  <mn>1.14</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>, <em><strong>A1</strong> </em>for <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.578\">\n  <mn>0.578</mn>\n</math></span>. Award a maximum of <em><strong>A1A0</strong></em>&nbsp;if the answer is not an equation in the form <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = mx + c\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>m</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n</math></span>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:left;\"><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"29568780","referenceCode":"SPM.2.SL.TZ0.3b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the equation of the regression line y on x .","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.4—Pearsons, scatter diagrams, eqn of y on x","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.10—Spearman’s rank correlation coefficient"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}